{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778547839,"nonce":"BfQOLa753o3oRA/ixWZmLUrXkXk=","message":"**Lit-replication 6-cell matrix (f47abb1) — negative result for faithful C\u0026S Eq. 15 schedule** (commit ceb3b87 on feature/lit-replication-results).\n\nKey cross-cutting findings from the 6-cell jerk × position-schedule matrix:\n\n1. **C\u0026S Eq. 15 (powerlaw (t/T)^6) does NOT reduce inter-replicate variance.** Within either jerk condition, powerlaw cells show vel-RMSE-ratio ≥ 1.09 (worse than flat). The intuition that late-trial-concentrated position loss funnels solutions does not hold under this matrix.\n\n2. **Shahbazi jerk regulariser (nn_output_jerk=1e5) does NOT funnel replicates either.** Within both flat and post-go schedules, jerk-off gives slightly BETTER vel-RMSE-ratio than jerk-on (Δ −0.18 and −0.14 respectively). Full-trial powerlaw is the one schedule where jerk on/off ties. Note: prior matrices showed jerk helping; this matrix (with correct hold penalty + nn_hidden_derivative=0.001) does not reproduce that effect.\n\n3. **No cell beats the prior 2bc95fd best (gru__jerk, 0.758).** Best here is `lit__flat_nojerk` at 0.978. **The lit-replication branch of the methodology-fix phase (b557d4e) does not produce a new production-loss candidate.**\n\n4. **Hold drift is the unfixed lever across the entire matrix.** Flat cells: 23-24 mm pre-go anticipation. Powerlaw cells: 2-3 mm (better, but never \u003c 0.5 mm). Cross-ref to the **conditional pre-go-mask follow-up** (will be filed as a new feature issue under `c99ad9d`): suggested starting weight `--nn-output-pre-go 1e-2` on the closest-to-threshold powerlaw cell.\n\nMechanism hypothesis (for the follow-up issue): the loss landscape with C\u0026S Eq. 15 + correct hold penalty has a flat-minimum basin where multiple replicate solutions are kinematically distinct but loss-equivalent; neither the jerk regulariser nor the (t/T)^6 weight schedule penalises the dimensions along which replicates diverge. A pre-go-mask term may help because it constrains the controller output on the hold epoch — a dimension that the running/hold/jerk terms all leave unconstrained.\n\nOut of scope here (does not motivate a coord-body change): tier reordering of any individual analysis, new training-method introduction, or a new adversary class.\n\nCross-ref: full results table + figures on f47abb1.","files":null}]}